h Faith|journal=The Aryeh Kaplan Anthology|volume=I|date=1994 }}\n* {{cite book|first=Menachem|last=Kellner|title=Dogma in Medieval Jewish Thought|url=https://archive.org/details/dogmainmedievalj0000kell|url-access=registration|place=London|publisher=Oxford University press|date=1986}}\n* {{cite journal|first=George Y.|last=Kohler|title=Reading Maimonides's Philosophy in 19th Century Germany|journal=Amsterdam Studies in Jewish Philosophy|volume=15|date=2012}}\n* {{cite book|first=Joel L.|last=Kraemer|title=Maimonides: The Life and World of One of Civilization's Greatest Minds|publisher=[[Doubleday (publisher)|Doubleday]]|date=2008}}\n* {{cite book|first=Daniel H.|last=Leaman|first2=Frank|last2=Leaman|first3=Oliver|last3=Leaman|title=History of Jewish Philosophy|edition=Second|place=London and New York|publisher=Routledge|date=2003|ref=pp.&nbsp;228\u2013378}} See especially chapters 10 through 15.\n*{{cite book |last=Maimonides |first= |author-link=Maimonides |title=[[Mishnah]], with Maimonides' Commentary |publisher=[[Mossad Harav Kook]] |translator=[[Yosef Qafih]] |volume=3 |edition= |date=1967|location=Jerusalem |page=|language=he |oclc=741081810 }}\n* {{cite book|first=Fred |last=Rosner |author-link=Fred Rosner|title=Maimonides's Medical Writings|volume=7 Vols|publisher=Maimonides Research Institute|date=1984\u20131994 }} (Volume 5 translated by Uriel Barzel; foreword by Fred Rosner.)\n* {{cite journal|first=David|last=Seidenberg|title=Maimonides \u2013 His Thought Related to Ecology|journal=The Encyclopedia of Religion and Nature|date=2005|url=http://neohasid.org/torah/rambam/ }}\n* {{cite journal|first=Marc B.|last=Shapiro|title=Maimonides Thirteen Principles: The Last Word in Jewish Theology?|journal=The Torah U-Maddah Journal|volume= 4|date=1993}}\n* {{cite book|first=Marc B.|last=Shapiro|title=Studies in Maimonides and His Interpreters|place=Scranton (PA)|publisher=University of Scranton Press|date=2008}}\n* {{cite book|first=Colette|last=Sirat|title=A Histo